| Notes                   = * Although the film was released in 2008, the comic tie-in {{cl|Marvel's The Avengers Prelude: Fury's Big Week Vol 1}} confirms that it is set in 2010, with the first half of this film occurring during the latter half of ''[[Iron Man 2 (film)|Iron Man 2]]'', along with ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]''.

| Trivia                  = * [[wikipedia:Zak Penn|Zak Penn]] wrote three original drafts of the film's script. [[wikipedia:Edward Norton|Edward Norton]] revised Zak's final script, seeing as Norton is a screenwriter too. Ultimately, the Writers Guild of America (WGA) gave sole credit to Penn.
* [[wikipedia:Martin Starr|Martin Starr]] appears in the film as an unnamed extra credited as "Computer Nerd" (and was only identified, as [[Amadeus Cho]], in the film's [[The Incredible Hulk (novel)|novelization]]). During a [[wikipedia:Reddit|Reddit]] Ask Me Almost Anything session, [[Marvel Studios]] President [[Kevin Feige]] revealed that Mr. Harrington and the "Computer Nerd" could be considered the same character.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/marvelstudios/comments/bp084n/hi_reddit_im_kevin_feige_amaa/enncmsh/|title=Hi reddit, I'm Kevin Feige. AMAA|work=Reddit|first=Kevin|last=Feige|date=16 May 2019|accessdate=18 May 2019}}

